Open],ExpressionUUID -> "6bf925c2-be0a-4fed-813c-23b963b574b9"],Cell[
TextData[{"Figure 1. The baryonic mass surface ",Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[RowBox[{StyleBox["M","TI"],"(",RowBox[
{StyleBox["v","TI"],",",StyleBox["r","TI"]}],")"}],TraditionalForm],"errors" -> {},
"input" -> "$M(v,r)$","state" -> "Boxes"],"TeXAssistantTemplate"],TraditionalForm]],
ExpressionUUID -> "b5dc99f6-d3b6-6d4b-87f4-62f4c0187c33"]," is shown as a function of orbital speed ",Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[StyleBox["v","TI"],TraditionalForm],
"errors" -> {},"input" -> "$v$","state" -> "Boxes"],"TeXAssistantTemplate"],TraditionalForm]],
ExpressionUUID -> "285d3e9c-f0d2-4f4a-9b9d-409fb26c1221"]," and orbital radius ",Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[StyleBox["r","TI"],TraditionalForm],
"errors" -> {},"input" -> "$r$","state" -> "Boxes"],"TeXAssistantTemplate"],TraditionalForm]],
ExpressionUUID -> "5acee3b7-498a-314e-bb37-f7d44f7d7f4a"]," for an illustrative acceleration scale ",Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[RowBox[{StyleBox["A","TI"],"\[LongEqual]",SuperscriptBox[
"10","-11"],StyleBox["m","TI"],SuperscriptBox[StyleBox["s","TI"],"-2"]}],TraditionalForm],
"errors" -> {},"input" -> "$A = 10^{-11} m s^{-2}$","state" -> "Boxes"],"TeXAssistantTemplate"],
TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID -> "d6fd2f66-596b-c24e-a241-1b7ca6ac09f9"],". The red ridge marks the locus ",Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[RowBox[{SubscriptBox[StyleBox[
"M","TI"],"max"],"(",StyleBox["v","TI"],")"}],TraditionalForm],"errors" -> {},"input" -> "$M_{\\max}(v)$",
"state" -> "Boxes"],"TeXAssistantTemplate"],TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID -> "7325711d-c20d-4440-9442-70b0c4c7cd6d"]," corresponding to the maximum baryonic mass permitted at each orbital speed. Galaxies populating this ridge reproduce the baryonic Tully--Fisher relation."}],
"Text",CellChangeTimes -> {{3.9800058728531036`*^9,3.980005952860935`*^9},{3.980006090516197`*^9,3.980006119709055`*^9},{3.9800063426269226`*^9,3.9800063464106216`*^9},{3.980006718065256`*^9,3.9800067332168217`*^9},{3.981659870041153`*^9,3.981659870184204`*^9},{3.9865602393160763`*^9,3.9865602395061665`*^9},{3.9865823646354885`*^9,3.9865823996584854`*^9},{3.9865824321582966`*^9,3.986582455127445`*^9},{3.9865825310225105`*^9,3.986582642283203`*^9},{3.9865826732213783`*^9,3.986582702653757`*^9},3.986582875872587`*^9},
ExpressionUUID -> "5be7e237-2b1b-7241-9bde-9b92a2319a4e"]},Open],ExpressionUUID -> "665094a3-261b-43ca-9bc5-f9be652e706d"],Cell[
CellGroupData[
{Cell[
"\<Baryonic Tully--Fisher Relation\>","Subsection",CellChangeTimes -> {{3.975926923007534`*^9,3.9759269671046143`*^9},3.9759270608007984`*^9,3.9765672182635574`*^9,3.9865804198203526`*^9},
ExpressionUUID -> "b87907b1-308d-a04b-85c8-aebde6086bba"],Cell[
TextData[{Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[RowBox[{SubscriptBox[StyleBox[
"M","TI"],"max"],"(",StyleBox["v","TI"],")"}],TraditionalForm],"errors" -> {},"input" -> "$M_{\\max}(v)$",
"state" -> "Boxes"],"TeXAssistantTemplate"],TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID -> "88181bd6-d6f0-5a46-9856-5fe0e872ec76"]," defines the scaling ",Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[RowBox[{StyleBox["M","TI"],"\[Proportional]",SuperscriptBox[
StyleBox["v","TI"],"4"]}],TraditionalForm],"errors" -> {},"input" -> "$M \\propto v^4$",
"state" -> "Boxes"],"TeXAssistantTemplate"],TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID -> "13f01bc9-a7fc-6c48-b6cb-b076a4303694"],", consistent with the observed baryonic Tully--Fisher relation. The normalization of this relation is set by the acceleration scale ",Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[StyleBox["A","TI"],TraditionalForm],
"errors" -> {},"input" -> "$A$","state" -> "Boxes"],"TeXAssistantTemplate"],TraditionalForm]],
ExpressionUUID -> "214ae725-7912-ac48-a0bb-338fd4b6cc6d"],". A characteristic acceleration scale in galaxy dynamics has previously been emphasized in frameworks such as MOND."}],
"Text",CellChangeTimes -> {{3.986580443860756`*^9,3.9865804573491364`*^9},{3.986580551566828`*^9,3.9865805678604546`*^9}},
ExpressionUUID -> "c32f4787-182f-b74f-8f91-ba79daf083a6"],Cell[
TextData[{"This parameter is determined empirically by fitting the circular-orbit envelope to the SPARC galaxy sample of McGaugh, Lelli and Schombert, using the assumptions ",Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[RowBox[{SubscriptBox["\[CapitalUpsilon]",
"\[FivePointedStar]"],"\[LongEqual]","0.5"}],TraditionalForm],"errors" -> {},"input" -> "$\\Upsilon_\\star=0.5$",
"state" -> "Boxes"],"TeXAssistantTemplate"],TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID -> "090fa05c-94f8-1544-b0ab-fd4e22e7d3f0"],", ",Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[RowBox[{SubscriptBox[StyleBox[
"f","TI"],StyleBox["gas",FontSlant -> "Plain"]],"\[LongEqual]","1.33"}],TraditionalForm],
"errors" -> {},"input" -> "$f_{\\mathrm{gas}}=1.33$","state" -> "Boxes"],"TeXAssistantTemplate"],
TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID -> "66a650b6-90ba-9e43-aa84-977f09b976c7"],", zero intrinsic mass-to-light uncertainty, and the quality cut ",Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[RowBox[{StyleBox["Qual",FontSlant -> "Plain"],"\[LessEqual]","3"}],
TraditionalForm],"errors" -> {},"input" -> "$\\mathrm{Qual}\\leq 3$","state" -> "Boxes"],
"TeXAssistantTemplate"],TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID -> "f5753233-ca91-f141-a807-b4d8146ba2fd"],". These rotationally supported disk systems are well suited to this analysis, as their kinematics closely follow circular-orbit behavior."}],
"Text",CellChangeTimes -> {{3.986580582861204`*^9,3.9865806413579426`*^9},{3.9865808728601665`*^9,3.9865808736898613`*^9}},
ExpressionUUID -> "f74d747d-863b-fb4b-8788-3de4d394a5ad"],Cell[
TextData[{"For each galaxy the rotation curve provides an asymptotic circular velocity ",Cell[
BoxData[
FormBox[TemplateBox[Association["boxes" -> FormBox[StyleBox["v","TI"],TraditionalForm],
"errors" -> {},"input" -> "$v$","state" -> "Boxes"],"TeXAssistantTemplate"],TraditionalForm]],
ExpressionUUID -> "63717763-d44b-df48-abf6-f4978d82e664"],", while the baryonic mass ",Cell[
BoxData[
